The paper discusses a resource allocation scheme for device-to-device (D2D) communication in cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed scheme uses a combinatorial auction mechanism, which involves game theory and optimization, making it relevant to the categories of game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the convergence and cheat-proof properties of the proposed scheme, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY).
